# pi-soul-agent — Architecture overview

## Purpose & stance
A Pi extension that manages SoulSpec personas. It is a learning port of `@vtstech/pi-soul`
from imperative Node into idiomatic Effect TS. Effect idiom (services, layers, Schema,
tagged errors, ManagedRuntime) is a first-class goal, not incidental.

## Module map
    .pi/extensions/soul.ts    entry: builds ManagedRuntime, wires layers, registers handlers
    src/commands.ts           /soul, /soul-list, /soul-info
    src/events.ts             session_start, resources_discover, before_agent_start, turn_end
    src/loader.ts             SoulSpecLoader service (discover/parse/filter/cache)
    src/persistence.ts        ActiveSoulPersistence service (~/.pi/agent/.active-soul.json)
    src/system-prompt.ts      buildSystemPrompt(manifest, level) — pure assembly
    src/types.ts              Effect Schema — source of truth for all soul.json shapes
    src/errors.ts             5 tagged errors; only SoulLoadError escapes the loader
    src/services/soul-fs.ts   expandHome, parseManifest, readJsonFile, readTextFile
    src/logger.ts             LoggerLayer + log{Debug,Info,Warning,Error}
    src/helpers/notify-ui.ts  safe ctx.ui.notify wrapper

## Runtime & layers (soul.ts)
A single ManagedRuntime is built once at module load. The layer stack provides
SoulSpecLoader.Default + ActiveSoulPersistence.Default over NodeFileSystem.layer +
NodePath layer + LoggerLayer.

## The event-handler bridge (the repeated seam)
Every handler follows one shape:
  1. build an Effect.gen pipeline (yield* services, do the work);
  2. runtime.runPromise(Effect.matchCause(pipeline, { onSuccess, onFailure }));
  3. map the tagged result back to Pi's callback world;
  4. surface errors via notifyUI(ctx, msg, level).
This isolates Effect's typed-error world behind runPromise at the callback boundary.

## Event handlers (events.ts)
  session_start       preload persisted Active Soul (reason startup|new); else advertise availability
  resources_discover  expose existing Search paths as promptPaths
  before_agent_start  inject buildSystemPrompt(activeSoul) appended to the base system prompt
  turn_end            heartbeat mala reminder (level-3 and heartbeatMode != off)

## Commands (commands.ts)
  /soul <name> [--level N] | off|clear | --help | --heartbeat <mode>   activate/deactivate/configure
  /soul-list                                                            list discovered souls (level-1)
  /soul-info [--full]                                                   show active soul; --full prints prompt

## Error model (errors.ts)
Internal: SoulNotFoundError, NoSoulsFoundError, ManifestParseError, FileSystemError.
Public: SoulLoadError — the only error that escapes the loader API; consumers handle one
tagged type via Effect.catchTag("SoulLoadError", ...).

## Open findings (UNVERIFIED — captured 2026-07-10, no failing test written yet)
- Heartbeat scheduler wedge (events.ts turn_end). `nextTurnAt` advances ONLY on the branch
  where a heartbeat actually fires (result.active === true). If the scheduled turn arrives
  while inactive (common case: no Soul active yet at turn 6), `nextTurnAt` freezes and the
  strict gate `totalTurns !== nextTurnAt` never matches again for the rest of the session;
  activating a level-3 Soul afterward does not recover it. Only session_start resets it.
  Write a failing test before any fix.
